TYPHOID FEVER UPDATE 2008 (07)
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

In this update:
[1] Philippines (Quezon)
[2] Uganda (Kasese)

******
[1] Philippines (Quezon)
Date: Mon 17 Nov 2008
Source: Balita [edited]
<http://balita.ph/2008/11/17/doh-probes-alleged-typhoid-outbreak-in-real-and-infanta-quezon/>


The Department of Health (DOH) on Monday [17 Nov 2008] said a team of
epidemiologists are now probing the alleged outbreak of typhoid fever
in the towns of Real and Infanta, Quezon province, which downed more
than 100 residents there.

DOH-National Epidemiology Center (NEC) director Eric Tayag said a
team of epidemiologists was sent there during the weekend [15-16 Nov
2008] to look into the incident and identify if the illness was
caused by typhoid fever or malaria. Reports said there were already
84 residents downed by the illness in Real town alone as of Monday
[17 Nov 2008].

Tayag said based on the preliminary findings of the DOH-Center for
Health and Development there, the victims displayed symptoms of
typhoid while others also have symptoms of malaria. "We still have to
wait for further updates from the team to declare a typhoid fever
outbreak. The result of the probe is expected to be released until
Friday [21 Nov 2008]," he said.

Tayag said health authorities are expecting the rise in the number of
cases as they haven't figured out the source of contaminated water.
The NEC team reportedly collected drinking water samples to determine
the cause of their illness. Tayag also advised residents of Real and
Infanta towns to boil their water to prevent the spread of the
water-borne disease.

--
